OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F424A1778490376
OL,3,CCouncil election results: Reform UK
OL,4,Cwin every seat on offer in Hartlepool
OL,6,FHer husband, the Hartlepool Labour MP
OL,7,FJonathan Brash, repeated his previous
OL,8,Fcalls for Sir Keir Starmer to stand
OL,9,Fdown.
OL,11,FHe said: "It's clear to me that the
OL,12,FPrime Minister should take this
OL,13,Fopportunity to set out a timetable for
OL,14,Fhis own departure, and then allow for
OL,15,Fthe widest possible leadership
OL,16,Felection that includes all the talents
OL,17,Fof our party."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G3/5
